         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" subtype="diplomatic" xml:id="juei0002.diplomatic" corresp="#juei0002.transcription #juei0002.translation">
            <p>+ ΚΥΡΙΟΣΦΥΛ<space dim="horizontal"/>ΑΞ<gap reason="illegible"/>
               <lb/>
                    ΟΔΟΝΣΟΥΟΥΤΗΝ<space dim="horizontal"/>ΕΞΟ<gap reason="illegible"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" subtype="transcription" xml:id="juei0002.transcription" corresp="#juei0002.diplomatic #juei0002.translation">
            <p>+ κύριος φυλάξ<supplied reason="lost">ει τὴν εἵσ</supplied>
               <lb/>
                    οδόν σου <ex>καὶ</ex> τὴν ἔξο<supplied reason="lost">δόν σου</supplied>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="juei0002.translation" corresp="#juei0002.diplomatic #juei0002.transcription">
            <p>(The) Lord will guard your entering and your departing.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>This inscription is a quotation of Psalms 120:8, a common church and entranceway
               epigraph. In line 2, the vertical alignment of omicron and upsilon is an abbreviation
               for καί.</p>
         </div>
